The paper describes a framework for distributed machine learning, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). However, the paper also focuses on the implementation of deep learning models, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
